<item>
            <title>[PIG-3573] Provide StoreFunc and LoadFunc for Accumulo</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3573</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Accumulo has some code to allow reading and writing from it through Pig. I&apos;ve been working on making it more robust and would like to try to get it included into Pig (to avoid the necessity to bundle additional jars).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some info on what currently exists &lt;a href=&quot;http://people.apache.org/~elserj/accumulo-pig/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://people.apache.org/~elserj/accumulo-pig/&lt;/a&gt;, and the current code &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=accumulo-pig.git&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=accumulo-pig.git&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Need to translate Maven build into Ant+Ivy&lt;br/&gt;
2. Need to figure out how to support Accumulo 1.4 and 1.5 builds (differences in dependencies and APIs)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
